 2& \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}$$ If $S  = \{(x, y): f \text{ is continous at point $( x, y)$}\}$, then set $S$ is A. Open B. Connected C. Closed D. Empty As $f$ is not continuous on the axes and is continuous at all other points. So set $S \neq \phi$. But how do I choose between other options?
